<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE concept PUBLIC "-//OASIS//DTD DITA Concept Doc//EN" "concept.dtd">
<concept id="my-concept">
  <title>Understanding DITA Topics</title>
  <shortdesc>This concept explains the basic structure of a DITA topic.</shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <abstract>DITA topics are the fundamental units of documentation in the <<!nav>>Darwin Information Typing Architecture<<!/nav>> (DITA).</abstract>
  </prolog>
  <body>
    <p>A DITA topic is an XML document that provides information on a single topic. It can be reused in various deliverables and organized using <<!nav>>DITA maps<<!/nav>>.</p>
    <p>DITA topics typically include:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>A title</li>
      <li>A short description</li>
      <li>A prolog (abstract or introductory information)</li>
      <li>A body (main content)</li>
      <li>Related links (navigation to other topics)</li>
    </ol>
    <example>
      <p>For example, a <tt>task</tt> topic describes a procedure, while a <tt>concept</tt> topic explains a concept or idea.</p>
    </example>
  </body>
</concept>
